    {
      "id": "graham-wealth",
      "text": "A startup is a company designed to grow fast. The only essential thing is growth. Everything else we associate with startups follows from growth.",
      "author": "Paul Graham",
      "author_slug": "graham",
      "source": "Startup = Growth, 2012",
      "categories": [
        "founder"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "startups",
        "growth",
        "definition"
      ],
      "grug_level": 2,
      "spiciness": 1
    },
    {
      "text": "Imposter syndrome means you're in the right room. If you're the smartest person in the room, you're in the wrong room.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "imposter-syndrome",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-imposter-syndrome-means-youre",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you're not embarrassed by your code from 6 months ago, you're not growing.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "improvement"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-youre-not-embarrassed",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to grow is to make your current customers successful. Happy customers bring new customers.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "marketing"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "customers"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-521",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your integrations page is your growth strategy. The more tools you connect, the more valuable you become.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "integrations",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-integrations-page-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indie hackers who talk to users grow faster than indie hackers who code in isolation.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "user-feedback",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-indie-hackers-who-talk",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your first 1000 email subscribers are the hardest to get. The next 9,000 are easier. Start collecting.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "marketing"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "email",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-first-1000-email",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to grow an indie business is to make your existing customers happier. New customers come from happy ones.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "satisfaction"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-666",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your first $1k in revenue is the hardest. The next $9k is easier. The next $90k is harder. The next $900k is the hardest.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "revenue",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-first-1k-in",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your biggest growth comes from your biggest failures. Embrace them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "failure",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-biggest-growth-comes",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Growth is never by mere chance; it is the result of forces working together.",
      "author": "James Cash Penney",
      "author_slug": "penney",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "forces"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "penney-growth-is-never-by",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your growth should be organic, not forced. Forced growth breaks things.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "organic"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-growth-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best growth comes from solving a problem so well that people tell their friends.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "satisfaction"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-growth-comes",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your growth rate matters less than your retention rate. A leaky bucket can't be filled.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "retention"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-growth-rate-matters",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your growth strategy should be unique to your business. Copying others' strategies is a recipe for mediocrity.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "uniqueness"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-growth-strategy-should",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best growth comes from compounding. Small improvements, consistently, over time.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "compounding"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-growth-comes-924",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best growth strategy is to make your product so good that marketing is optional.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "marketing"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "product"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-growth-strategy",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best leaders are the ones who make others better. Not just themselves.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "leadership",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-leaders-are-1034",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to grow an indie project is to make your users successful. Their success is your success.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "growth",
        "success"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-1054",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your indie project is your baby. Take care of it. Feed it. Grow it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "care",
        "growth"
      ],
